{
  "text": "We have recently described a new form of hereditary ataxia, IOSCA [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The clinical symptoms in this syndrome include cerebellar ataxia associated with peripheral sensory neuropathy, cerebral symptoms including athetosis and epilepsy, deafness, ophthalmoplegia, optic atrophy, and, in females, primary hypogonadism. We have identified 19 patients with this recessively in-",
